2π/n + \frac{π - 2π/n}{2} = π\frac{2/n + 1}{2} = π(\frac1n + \frac12)
⟨φ', φ⟩ = ||φ'||\cdot||φ||\cos π(\frac1n+\frac12) ≕ ||φ'||\cdot||φ||\cdot C
2⟨φ', φ⟩ = ⟨φ, φ⟩' = (||φ||^2)' = 2||φ||\cdot||φ||'
 ||φ||' = C||φ'||
φ' = r'(\cos α, \sin α) + rα'(-\sin α, \cos α)
v = ||φ'|| = -r' + rα' = -Cv + rα'
α' = \frac{v(1+C)}{r} = \frac{v(1+C)}{r_0 + Cvt}
α = \frac{v(1+C)}{Cv}\ln r = (\frac1C+1)\ln r\\r = \exp\left(\frac{α}{\frac1C+1}\right)
